message.content:
First, make sure that your server is off.

1) Rename current `world` folder to different name (by your choice).
2) Main goal - compress it locally and upload archive to server, afterwards comes 2 options:
2.1) if archive size is less than 100MB, then you can upload directly from Control Panel (in File Manager you will see button `Upload files`)
2.2) if archive size is bigger than 100MB, then you need to upload it, using SFTP (details here: https://discord.com/channels/697340602504970261/774615671488249908/831125487526346755)
3) Once that's done, go to File Manager (in Control Panel), find your archive, next to it (in right side) you'll see 3 dots, click on them, select `Unarchive`.
4) After that rename your uncompressed folder to `world`.

Now you can start server.
